Title: Ghotic Lolita
Description: (ゴスロリ) is a style of Lolita that is primarily influenced by victorian-inspired Goth styles. The style was popularized by Mana, a japanese musician.

Title: Sweet Lolita
Description: (甘ロリ) is a style of Lolita that contains features nearly exclusive to Lolita. It is also the most child-like of the styles, using many bows, ruffles and light colors to make up an outfit.

Title: Classic Lolita
Description: (クラロリ) is a style of Lolita that is highly inspired by historic fashion. It radiates the elegance of a victorian lady, and appears more mature than other Lolita styles.

Title: Elegant Lolita
Description: The Elegant Gothic Lolita wears an outfit that makes her look like a Victorian doll: puffy skirts, lots of frills, bonnets, huge ribbons, mostly black. There's also shades of Alice in Wonderland (though it is beginning to fall out of favor), with the aforementioned dark motif. On occasion, her hair may be in Regal Ringlets or Ojou Ringlets.

Title: Qi/Wa Lolita
Description: (チーロリ) is a style of Lolita that is the combination with Chinese qipao. It is similar to the more common Wa Lolita, which combines traditional Japanese clothing with Lolita. It is also refered to as Han Lolita (華ロリ) when being based on hanfu.

Title: Hime Lolita
Description: (姫ロリ) is a style of Lolita that focuses on a princess-like appearance that is often OTT. It can look very similar to Classic Lolita, but there are many decorative elements borrowed from Sweet.

Title: Punk Lolita
Description: (パンクロリ) is a style of Lolita that is inspired by western Punk fashion and also one of the most challenging.

Title: Kawaii Lolita
Description: (ナチュロリ), also known as Mori Lolita, is a style of Lolita that is the combination with Mori Girl which revolves around natural and vintage materials. The name and style was first coined by the brand MiELette Tautou.
